{"pageProps":{"note":{"id":"GvwoAWaYZxq1czYi3t3k4","title":"Factor Models","vault":{"fsPath":"vault"},"type":"note","desc":"","links":[],"anchors":{"factor-models":{"type":"header","text":"Factor Models","value":"factor-models","line":8,"column":0},"model-notation":{"type":"header","text":"Model Notation","value":"model-notation","line":14,"column":0},"classical-factor-mode":{"type":"header","text":"Classical Factor Mode","value":"classical-factor-mode","line":27,"column":0},"":{"type":"header","text":"","value":"","line":30,"column":0}},"fname":"Factor-Models","updated":1634876621699,"created":1634735821990,"parent":"PhD","children":[],"data":{},"contentHash":"8f4b1a76393c9ab5300fa932b63c4e5c","custom":{}},"body":"<h1 id=\"factor-models\"><a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading\" href=\"#factor-models\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\"><use xlink:href=\"#svg-link\"></use></svg></a>Factor Models</h1>\n<h1 id=\"factor-models-1\"><a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading\" href=\"#factor-models-1\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\"><use xlink:href=\"#svg-link\"></use></svg></a>Factor Models</h1>\n<p>This section gives a broad overview over factor models.</p>\n<p>Most of this is more focused on giving a historical overview, and as such as a higher focus on Classical Factor Models. More more relevant and up to date literature, see Static Factor Models (PCA), or Dynamic Factor Models (Dynamic PCA).</p>\n<h2 id=\"model-notation\"><a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading\" href=\"#model-notation\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\"><use xlink:href=\"#svg-link\"></use></svg></a>Model Notation</h2>\n<p>We begin with the simplest factor model representation:</p>\n<div class=\"math math-display\"><span class=\"katex-display\"><span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" display=\"block\"><semantics><mrow><msub><mi>X</mi><mrow><mi>i</mi><mi>t</mi></mrow></msub><mo>=</mo><msub><mi>C</mi><mrow><mi>i</mi><mi>t</mi></mrow></msub><mo>+</mo><msub><mi>e</mi><mrow><mi>i</mi><mi>t</mi></mrow></msub></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">X_{it} = C_{it} + e_{it}</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.83333em;vertical-align:-0.15em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.07847em;\">X</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t vlist-t2\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.31166399999999994em;\"><span style=\"top:-2.5500000000000003em;margin-left:-0.07847em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mtight\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal mtight\">i</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal mtight\">t</span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"vlist-s\">​</span></span><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.15em;\"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2777777777777778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">=</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2777777777777778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.83333em;vertical-align:-0.15em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.07153em;\">C</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t vlist-t2\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.31166399999999994em;\"><span style=\"top:-2.5500000000000003em;margin-left:-0.07153em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mtight\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal mtight\">i</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal mtight\">t</span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"vlist-s\">​</span></span><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.15em;\"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2222222222222222em;\"></span><span class=\"mbin\">+</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2222222222222222em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.58056em;vertical-align:-0.15em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">e</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t vlist-t2\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.31166399999999994em;\"><span style=\"top:-2.5500000000000003em;margin-left:0em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mtight\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal mtight\">i</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal mtight\">t</span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"vlist-s\">​</span></span><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.15em;\"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></div>\n<p>where <span class=\"math math-inline\"><span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><msub><mi>X</mi><mrow><mi>i</mi><mi>t</mi></mrow></msub></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">X_{it}</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.83333em;vertical-align:-0.15em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.07847em;\">X</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t vlist-t2\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.31166399999999994em;\"><span style=\"top:-2.5500000000000003em;margin-left:-0.07847em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mtight\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal mtight\">i</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal mtight\">t</span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"vlist-s\">​</span></span><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.15em;\"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span> is decomposed into common component <span class=\"math math-inline\"><span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><msub><mi>C</mi><mrow><mi>i</mi><mi>t</mi></mrow></msub></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">C_{it}</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.83333em;vertical-align:-0.15em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.07153em;\">C</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t vlist-t2\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.31166399999999994em;\"><span style=\"top:-2.5500000000000003em;margin-left:-0.07153em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mtight\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal mtight\">i</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal mtight\">t</span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"vlist-s\">​</span></span><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.15em;\"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span> that is orthogonal to the idiosyncratic error <span class=\"math math-inline\"><span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><msub><mi>e</mi><mrow><mi>i</mi><mi>t</mi></mrow></msub></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">e_{it}</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.58056em;vertical-align:-0.15em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">e</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t vlist-t2\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.31166399999999994em;\"><span style=\"top:-2.5500000000000003em;margin-left:0em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mtight\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal mtight\">i</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal mtight\">t</span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"vlist-s\">​</span></span><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.15em;\"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span>.</p>\n<p>If <span class=\"math math-inline\"><span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><msub><mi>e</mi><mrow><mi>i</mi><mi>t</mi></mrow></msub></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">e_{it}</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.58056em;vertical-align:-0.15em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">e</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t vlist-t2\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.31166399999999994em;\"><span style=\"top:-2.5500000000000003em;margin-left:0em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mtight\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal mtight\">i</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal mtight\">t</span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"vlist-s\">​</span></span><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.15em;\"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span> is assumed to strictly independent (mutually orthogonal across all <span class=\"math math-inline\"><span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>i</mi><mo separator=\"true\">,</mo><mi>t</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">i, t</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.85396em;vertical-align:-0.19444em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">i</span><span class=\"mpunct\">,</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.16666666666666666em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">t</span></span></span></span></span>), this leads to the so called \"exact\" or \"strong factor model\" initially considered by Geweke and Sargent and Sims. Although this, in conjunction with a standard gaussian assumption on the error terms leads to straightfoward estimation via ML/Kalman filter, it is understandably completely unrealistic.</p>\n<h2 id=\"classical-factor-mode\"><a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading\" href=\"#classical-factor-mode\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\"><use xlink:href=\"#svg-link\"></use></svg></a>Classical Factor Mode</h2>\n<p>ls</p>\n<h2 id=\"\"><a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading\" href=\"#\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\"><use xlink:href=\"#svg-link\"></use></svg></a></h2>","noteIndex":{"id":"PhD","title":"PhD Homepage","vault":{"fsPath":"vault"},"type":"note","desc":"","links":[{"type":"wiki","from":{"fname":"root","id":"PhD","vaultName":"vault"},"value":"roadmap","alias":"roadmap","position":{"start":{"line":12,"column":1,"offset":451},"end":{"line":12,"column":12,"offset":462},"indent":[]},"xvault":false,"sameFile":false,"to":{"fname":"roadmap"}},{"type":"wiki","from":{"fname":"root","id":"PhD","vaultName":"vault"},"value":"Meeting","alias":"Meeting","posit